The value of the pound rises as UK wage growth accelerates
The value of the pound jumped after the numbers showed an increase in UK wage growth, and at the same time the FTSE 100 index rose with the bid target SABMiller.
Between May and July, UK wages, excluding bonuses, rose by 2.9 percent compared to the same period last year.
The rate of growth was the fastest since 2009 and was considered to bring with it estimates of rising rates.
The pound rose more than 1% against the dollar to $1,5505, and 0.84% against the euro to €1,3730.
