In the last four years, the ingestion of hand sanitizer by children has increased fourfold
Poison data centers across the United States have reported a nearly 400% increase in the ingestion of heavily alcoholic hand sanitizer in children under the age of 12 since 2010, according to the Georgia Poison Data Center.
